<h1>Book Summaries</h1>

Summaries/digests of recent books relative to the practice of computer
science research and industry.  Summaries written by <a
href="http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~fox/">Armando Fox</a> unless otherwise
noted.  If a summary is absent, I haven't finished the book yet.

<h3>Software and System Design</h3>

<ul>
  <li> Nancy Leveson,
       <i>Safeware: System Safety and Computers.</i>
       Addison-Wesley, 1995.
       <a href="safeware.html">AF</a>
  <li> Nathan Borenstein,
       <i>Programming As If People Mattered</i>.
       <a href="paipm.html">AF</a>
</ul>

<h3>Software Industry</h3>

<ul>
  <li> Jim McCarthy,
       <i>Dynamics of Software Development</i>.
       Seattle: Microsoft Press, 1996.
       <a href="dynsofdev.html">AF</A>

  <li> Andy Grove,
       <i>High Output Management</i>.

  <li> Geoffrey Moore,
       <i>Inside the Tornado</i>.
</ul>

